OL,5,Canalysis
OL,7,FRory Boland, editor of magazine Which?
OL,8,FTravel, said: "While inflation has
OL,9,Fstarted to ease over the last year,
OL,10,Four latest research has shown holiday
OL,11,Fprices bucking the trend, with a
OL,12,Fcombination of increased demand,
OL,13,Falongside rising energy and fuel
OL,14,Fcosts, contributing to higher prices
OL,15,Ffor holidaymakers.
OL,17,F"Booking early is almost always your
OL,18,Fbest chance of securing the best rate
OL,19,F` so now is the best time to get the
OL,20,Fcheapest prices on summer holidays.
